1245.long_description: A yard of ale has been left here by some foolish person.

1246.name: mining lantern
1246.long_description: A brass lantern, typical of the style used in mines. Its light flickering gently.

1251.name: old shields
1251.short_description: Remnants of ancient heroes and glories.
1251.long_description: Remnants of ancient heroes and glories.

1255.name: huge crystal
1255.short_description: You gaze into the crystal for a while, but even your finely honed mind cannot follow the action within.
1255.long_description: You gaze into the crystal for a while, but even your finely honed mind cannot follow the action within.

1256.name: small door
1256.long_description: It leads to the chamber of the arch-magi
1256.takeFail: It's small, but you still can't remove it.

1257.name: gold door
1257.long_description: It bears the runes for World and Holding. It is closed.

1258.name: mighty door
1258.long_description: The mighty doors stand closed to the south.

1266.name: old runes
1266.short_description: The runes are difficult to follow and decipher, but seem to be directions to some of the arcane magical arts, and detail some of the movements to be associated with spells.
1266.long_description: The runes are difficult to follow and decipher, but seem to be directions to some of the arcane magical arts, and detail some of the movements to be associated with spells.

1269.name: small well
1269.short_description: It appears to have dried up.
1269.long_description: It appears to have dried up.
1269.takeFail: Taking the well would be silly.

1274.name: stone coffin
1274.short_description: It bears the words 'Open not, lest foul undead slay thee.'
1274.long_description: A stone coffin is set on a plinth in the centre of the chamber. The coffin is open.

1276.name: old dust
1276.long_description: The thick dust on the floor shows you are the only person to have come this way for a long time.
1276.takeFail: You pick up some dust and blow it off your hand, forming an impressive cloud.

1280.name: dilapidated door
1280.long_description: The door is old and battered, worn by the weather and by time.
1280.takeFail: You yank at the door, but it remains fixed on its hinges.

1281.name: wooden sign
1281.short_description: It is battered and has seen too many years exposure to the driving salt soaked winds that howl in from the sea.
1281.long_description: It is battered and has seen too many years exposure to the driving salt soaked winds that howl in from the sea.

1284.name: spit
1284.long_description: A pig roasts on a spit above the roaring fire.
1284.takeFail: Taking it while it's roasting hot would not be a good idea.

1286.name: inn door
1286.takeFail: You heave at the door, but are unable to pull it off its hinges.

1288.name: log bench
1288.takeFail: It's much too big and heavy.

1289.name: inn table
1289.long_description: Good solid tables. Only slight evidence of ale spillage. There is a pack of cards and a Morris board here.
1289.takeFail: You try to take the table, but only look foolish because it's too large to carry.

1291.name: sack
1291.short_description: An old rather rotten looking sack has been dumped here.
1291.long_description: It seems in better condition than at first sight, but it is still not in great condition.
1291.takeFail: It's so rotten looking, you don't want to take it.

1293.name: large window
1293.short_description: A huge window looks out across the snows.
1293.long_description: It looks out over the snows. You could climb out of the window and down the snowbanks outside, providing of course they will take your weight. It is difficult to tell if they will though.
1293.climbThrough: With considerable effort you scramble through the window.|You scramble inelegantly through the window.|You squeeze through the open window.

1295.name: large window
1295.short_description: You could climb up and through it quite easily.
1295.long_description: A large window is set high up above the snowbanks on one side.
1295.climbThrough: With considerable effort you scramble through the window.|You scramble inelegantly through the window.|You squeeze through the open window.

1296.name: stone tablet
1296.short_description: An ancient stone tablet has been left here.
1296.long_description: The tablet is an ancient piece from the philosopher-mage Theosynimus. It bears the words 'Thrice at the lich-owl's screech, cast fire into the images of the moon, listen well lest bitter experience teach, none make the path of the shadow alone.'

1299.name: small rock
1299.short_description: A small piece of rock lies here.
1299.long_description: A small piece of rock has been left on a stone slab.

1300.name: hammer
1300.short_description: A heavy mining hammer has been left here.
1300.long_description: Very heavy, not the sort of hammer to hit your fingers with, more for hitting other peoples.

1301.name: pick
1301.long_description: A heavy pick has been put here. The pick is battered and worn, and obviously much used.

1302.name: shed door
1302.long_description: The shed door is closed.|It is a typical door.
1302.takeFail: You try to take the shed door, but it's too securely fastened on its hinges.

1303.name: stout door
1303.long_description: The shed door is closed.|It is a typical door.
1303.takeFail: You try to take the door, but it's too securely fastened on its hinges.

1304.name: quarry shed
1304.short_description: It appears to be a store for all the quarrying equipment.
1304.long_description: A large stone built shed stands at the north end of the quarry.|It appears to be a store for all the quarrying equipment.
1304.takeFail: Taking the whole shed would be silly.

1316.name: still pool
1316.long_description: The gentle swaying of the trees, and their reflection in the pool, make this place seem quiet and peaceful.

1322.name: old fire
1322.short_description: The fire is quite old, several days at least.
1322.long_description: Someone has had a fire here recently, although all that is left now is a pile of ashes. Someone has spread the ashes out too.|The fire is quite old, several days at least.
1322.takeFail: You pick up some ashes and blow them off your hand.

1324.name: portable hole
1324.short_description: There is a large hole here.
1324.long_description: It is a strange hole. It seems almost well, unattached.
1324.takeFail: You can't get a hold of it.

1327.name: tomb lid
1327.open_description: With a sound of grinding stone you open the tomb lid
1327.close_description: You close the tomb lid with a thud

1328.name: mystic talisman
1328.short_description: It appears to be a marker for some kind of magic.
1328.long_description: An ancient engraved stone talisman has been placed here.|It appears to be a marker for some kind of magic.

1329.name: large tomb
1329.short_description: The tomb is very solidly built from stone slabs.
1329.long_description: A large stone tomb is set in the very centre of the chamber. The tomb is closed.|The tomb is very solidly built from stone slabs. It is closed.
1329.open_description: With a sound of grinding stone you open the tomb lid
1329.close_description: You close the tomb lid with a thud

1340.name: wooden boat
1340.long_description: An old wooden boat has been left here.|It's in good condition.
1340.takeFail: You can't carry the boat, but perhaps you could row it.
1340.climbThrough: You climb aboard and push off into the lake.

1343.name: icy passage
1343.short_description: An icy passage is closed, leading north into a cave.
1343.long_description: An icy passage is closed, leading north into a cave.

1345.name: icy passage
1345.short_description: An icy passage has to a huge icy hall extending away southwards is closed.
1345.long_description: An icy passage has to a huge icy hall extending away southwards is closed.

1347.name: frozen corpse
1347.long_description: A stiff and frozen human corpse lies slumped on the ground.

1348.name: narrow cavemouth
1348.long_description: The opening appears to lead into a cave.

1349.name: icy cavemouth
1349.long_description: The cavemouth is blocked up by a huge fall of snow.

1351.name: piles of snow
1351.long_description: The snow is deep and movement awkward. There appears to have been an avalanche here recently. A narrow path leads east and steeply up into a side valley.
1351.takeFail: You can't carry that much snow.

1353.name: wooden bridge
1353.long_description: Across the bridge the path continues south along the other side of the pass.
1353.takeFail: To your surprise you find that you can't carry a bridge.

1355.name: old bridge
1355.long_description: An old wooden bridge carries the path westwards across the foaming waters onto the other side of the pass. The bridge looks in good condition, and is probably fairly safe. If not then its a long way to fall into foaming ice cold water....
1355.takeFail: To your surprise you find that you can't carry a bridge.

1366.name: shortsword
1366.long_description: A sharp shortsword.|A strong stabbing weapon.

1367.name: small dagger
1367.short_description: Although small it is very sharp.
1367.long_description: A small dagger has been dropped here.|Although small it is very sharp.

1368.name: door
1368.long_description: The west door is closed.|It is a stout door.
1368.takeFail: You try to remove the door, but it's securely hinged.

1369.name: door
1369.long_description: A good stout door. It is closed.
1369.takeFail: You try to remove the door, but it's securely hinged.

1371.name: old horseshoe
1371.short_description: Well it didnt bring the horse any luck.
1371.long_description: An old horseshoe has been discarded here.|Well it didnt bring the horse any luck.

1374.name: runesword
1374.short_description: A huge black runesword lies at your feet, glowing with arcane power.
1374.long_description: A huge black runesword stands upright before you, embedded in the solid stone altar.

1378.name: iron lever
1378.short_description: It is connected to a mass of heavy mechanisms.
1378.long_description: A huge iron lever in the west wall has been pulled up in its slot.
1378.takeFail: You make strenuous efforts to remove the lever, but only look foolish in the process.

1379.name: oak door
1379.long_description: An open oak door leads east into the gatehouse.
1379.takeFail: You try to remove the door from its hinges, but find that's not possible.

1380.name: oak door
1380.takeFail: You try to remove the door from its hinges, but find that's not possible.

1382.name: strong portcullis
1382.short_description: It is strong and bound in heavy iron.
1382.long_description: The portcullis is raised, allowing free access to and from the castle.
1382.takeFail: Even if you could remove it - which you can't - you couldn't carry a portcullis.

1384.name: portcullis
1384.long_description: It is strong and bound in heavy iron.
1384.takeFail: Even if you could remove it - which you can't - you couldn't carry a portcullis.

1385.name: red hat
1385.long_description: The red fedora hat looks about your size.

1386.name: wizard hat
1386.long_description: The wizard hat is tall, with a large floppy brim.

1387.name: witch hat
1387.long_description: The witch hat is black and tall, with a large round brim.

1388.name: granite statue
1388.long_description: The ominous black granite statue in the shape of a giant aquatic bird casts a long shadow down the hall. Its surface is smooth and polished.
1388.takeFail: It's attractive, but you could never carry anything that large.

1389.name: amber pendant
1389.short_description: A small polished amber pendant lies here.
1389.long_description: A small polished amber pendant, on leather strap.
1389.open_description: You fasten the amber pendant around your neck
1389.close_description: You unfasten the amber pendant from your neck and stow it

1390.name: leather bracelet
1390.long_description: The leather bracelet has a cross hatch pattern on it.
1390.open_description: You put on the leather bracelet

1391.name: leather arm guard
1391.long_description: The leather arm guard is ornately patterned and laced together.
1391.open_description: You put on the leather arm guard and fasten its laces
1391.close_description: You unfasten the laces of the arm guard and remove it

1392.name: falconry glove
1392.long_description: A large falconry glove made from dark brown leather.
1392.open_description: You put on the falconry glove

1397.name: longbow arrows
1397.long_description: Arrows for a longbow. Increasing in diameter towards the bodkin tips with goose feather fletchings.

1341.name: heralds staff
1341.long_description: The staff is made from bronze, with curved prongs at the top reminiscent of a bull's horns.

1342.name: iron cauldron
1342.long_description: The iron cauldron is suspended on three chains from a frame over the fireplace. Elaborate etchings around the rim of the cauldron depict the mythic saga of a water goddess
1342.takeFail: It's much too heavy to carry.
1342.open_description: You remove the lid of the cauldron
1342.open_failed_description: You can't remove the lid of the cauldron
1342.close_description: You place the lid back on the cauldron

1402.name: hearth
1402.long_description: A small square charcoal hearth is at the centre of the house, surrounded by neatly arranged bowls and utensils.

1344.name: wooden stool
1344.long_description: The wooden stool is made from a slice of tree trunk with conspicuous rings and has three stubby legs.

1401.name: rustic stool
1401.long_description: The rustic stool is made from a chunky slice of tree trunk with conspicuous rings and has three short legs.

1346.name: tannur
1346.long_description: A clay tannur is at the centre of the house, used for baking.

1400.name: bronze sword
1400.long_description: The bronze sword is polished and shines brightly. Its has a convex cutting blade.

1403.name: bronze dagger
1403.long_description: The small polished bronze dagger has an elaborately patterned grip with three sets of concentric circles either side.|The bronze dagger is carefully polished and looks like it may be primarily a status symbol for its owner. It has elaborate circular markings on the handle.

1404.name: small wooden shield
1404.long_description: The small wooden shield is round and made from a few joined planks with a metallic button in the middle.

1405.name: goddess shield
1405.short_description: A small shield with goddess face carved on it.
1405.long_description: The small shield is round and made from a interlocking wooden pieces. It is elaborately carved with the angry face of a goddess. Curls of her voluminous hair radiate out towards its circumference.

1406.name: woolen jacket
1406.long_description: A thick woolen jacket with tartan patterning.
1406.open_description: You put on the woolen jacket
1406.close_description: You take off the woolen jacket

1407.name: stone hearth
1407.long_description: The hearth has a flat clay surface on top of a pile of stones.

1408.name: iron torc
1408.long_description: Made from pleated iron with loops on each end to fasten a cape. The torc is unremarkable but functional.

1409.name: golden torc
1409.long_description: Made from a single spiral twisted strip of gold, the torc makes a striking fashion accessory.

1410.name: arcane ring
1410.short_description: The ring is jet black and has a celtic knot pattern around the outside.
1410.long_description: The ring is jet black and has a celtic knot pattern around the outside.

1411.name: crystal dagger
1411.short_description: The crystal dagger is carved from quartz.
1411.long_description: The carved quartz crystal dagger dazzles brightly.

1412.name: descending staircase
1412.short_description: A descending spiral staircase has been cut into the rock.
1412.long_description: A descending spiral staircase has been cut into the rock.
1412.jumpTo: You take a running jump across the chasm onto the stairs.|You leap across the chasm onto the stairs

1413.name: leather tabard
1413.short_description: The sleaveless leather tabard is fastened with a ribbon around the waist. Standard attire for a guild artisan.
1413.long_description: The sleaveless leather tabard is fastened with a ribbon around the waist. Standard attire for a guild artisan.
1413.open_description: You put on the leather tabard and tie the waist ribbon around your back.
1413.close_description: You unfasten the waist ribbon and take off the leather tabard

1415.name: ancient stone statue
1415.long_description: Crudely carved out of sandstone and resting on a plinth the ram's head statue with its giant curling horns glares at you.
1415.takeFail: It's too heavy to move, let alone carry.

1416.name: honeycombs
1416.short_description: The honeycombs are swarming with hundreds of bees. So many that you can hardly see their hexagonal cells underneath|Bees scurry around busily on the honeycombs
1416.long_description: The honeycombs is swarming with hundreds of bees. So many that you can hardly see their hexagonal cells underneath|Bees scurry around busily on the honeycombs
1416.takeFail: Carrying an angry swarm of bees is probably not a great idea.

1417.name: pentangle pendant
1417.short_description: A silver pentangle on a leather neck strap
1417.long_description: A silver pentangle on a leather neck strap

1418.name: wooden table
1418.short_description: A wooden tavern table build from solid planks. There is a pack of cards here.
1418.long_description: A wooden tavern table build from solid planks. There is a pack of cards and a Nine Men's Morris board here.
1418.takeFail: Stealing the table from this seedy locale would not be a wise move.

1419.name: pear
1419.long_description: A fresh looking pear.|Looks quite edible.

1422.name: wall calendar
1422.long_description: An old and faded calendar hangs from the lab wall. The days of the month contain hastily scribbled illegible handwriting. One entry which you can vaguely discern is headed 'initial coin offering', followed by some mathematical calculation you don't understand.
1422.takeFail: The calendar is so fragile that if you tried to take it then it would disintegrate.

1423.name: feast bench
1423.short_description: A modest feast bench has been set out here.
1423.long_description: A modest feast bench has been set out here. It has a couple of shelves for fruit and confectionaries.
1423.takeFail: The feast bench is much too large to carry.

1424.name: bowl of soup
1424.short_description: A modest wooden bowl of broth
1424.long_description: A modest wooden bowl of broth

1425.name: shipwreck
1425.short_description: The barnacle encrusted remains of a ship, long ago wrecked and partially buried in the sand
1425.long_description: The barnacle encrusted remains of a ship, long ago wrecked and partially buried in the sand
1425.takeFail: The shipwreck is much too big to take.
1425.climbThrough: You scramble up onto the shipwreck

1427.long_description: A long pole with a vicious-looking metal spike and straight edged chopper on the end of it

1428.long_description: The chainmail shirt made from small iron rings is heavy but will protect against cutting weapons

1428.close_description: You pull off the chainmail shirt over your head

1429.long_description: The chainmail vest made from small steel rings is heavy but will protect against cutting weapons

1429.close_description: You pull off the chainmail shirt over your head
